2. Fiber Architecture (React 16)
	â€¢	Fiber = new reconciliation engine (2017).
	â€¢	Each component is represented by a Fiber node (a JS object with props, state, effects, etc).
	â€¢	Key advantage: React can split rendering into small units of work.
	â€¢	Work can be:
	â€¢	Started
	â€¢	Paused
	â€¢	Resumed
	â€¢	Abandoned

ğŸ‘‰ Interview note: â€œFiber was introduced so React can break long tasks into chunks, allowing the browser to stay responsive.â€

