3. Scheduler
	â€¢	React has a scheduler (separate package) to decide which work to do first.
	â€¢	Assigns priorities:
	â€¢	Immediate â†’ Clicks, input events.
	â€¢	User-blocking â†’ Typing, animations.
	â€¢	Normal â†’ UI updates, data rendering.
	â€¢	Low â†’ Preloading data, background work.
	â€¢	Idle â†’ Non-critical tasks.

ğŸ‘‰ Interview note: â€œThe scheduler ensures urgent user interactions always go first.â€

